<TITLE> Navy chief Sarwar Jahan Nizam attends reunion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 25 (bdnews24.com)At a reunion of retired and active officers of Bangladesh Navy held at Naval Headquarters Multipurpose Hall Thursday night, the Chief of Naval Staff Vice Admiral Sarwar Jahan Nizam thanked all retired officers, urging them to build a hearty relationship with the officers of new generation, an ISPR press release issued Friday said. The naval chief also advised the active officers to enrich their knowledge and gather experience from the retired officers. Subsequently, the Vice Admiral also proposed to establish a Retired Naval Officers Welfare Association (RNOWA). Ex Naval Chiefs, Ex Presidents of Bangladesh Navy Family Welfare Association, retired naval officers and their spouses and senior officers of Naval Headquarters attended the programme. bd
